#: .\units\EE_units\monsters.cfg:31
msgid ""
"The term “monster” incorporates many hideous beasts that haunt the caves, "
"wilderness, ocean depths, and other climes of the world. They figure largely "
"in the tales and nightmares of its denizens, as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dwarvish Fighter
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a1-Fighter.cfg:9
msgid ""
"This unit is from Extended Era. Its coding and art were done by the Various "
"people who created Extended Era."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dwarvish Fighter
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_triththa_Dwarvish_Fighter
#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a1-Fighter.cfg:9
#: .\units\EOS_units\dwarves\Fighter.cfg:11
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Fighter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Dwarvish Fighters wield mighty battle axes and hammers, which make them "
"feared opponents in close-range combat. They are excellent in mountainous "
"terrain or underground. Their power and endurance more than compensate for "
"their relatively poor mobility."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Runesmith, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a2-Runesmith.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Runesmith"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Runesmith, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a2-Runesmith.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Dwarvish runesmiths, now practiced at their craft, carve arcane runes into "
"their weapons and armor. These runes infuse the runesmith's blows with power "
"and accuracy, and disrupt the blows of their enemies, causing them to strike "
"softly, weakly and on the armor of the defender."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Runemaster, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a3-Runemaster.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Runemaster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Runemaster, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a3-Runemaster.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Except for those with almost supernatural skill, the highest rank a "
"runecrafter can rise to is that of the Dwarvish Runemaster. Striking blows "
"nearly as powerful as those of the best warriors, they would be fearsome "
"without their craft, but with it they are also nigh on invincible, since "
"their runes cause the physical blows of their enemies to deal less damage "
"than would be expected."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Arcanister, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a4-Arcanister.cfg:5
msgid "Dwarvish Arcanister"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_dwarves_Dwarvish_Arcanister, race=dwarf
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\a4-Arcanister.cfg:25
msgid ""
"The most powerful of all the runecrafters, the Dwarvish Arcanister destroys "
"wounded enemies almost instantly, and rarely fails to cause a wound when that"
" is his intent. His skill in runecrafting is unrivaled, and the glyphs he "
"carves into his weapons and armor deflect the blows of his enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Dwarvish Thunderer
#: .\units\EE_units\dwarves\b1-Thunderer.cfg:9
msgid ""
"When the men of Wesnoth first encountered the dwarves, they were mystified by"
" the power of the Dwarvish Thunderers, who were able to hurl death from afar "
"through the apparatus of these strange wands they carried into battle. The "
"deafening noise of these ‘thundersticks’ is terrifying to behold, and is made"
" more so by the secrecy which dwarves wrap about their workings."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Baby_Bigfoot, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Baby_Bigfoot.cfg:4
msgid "Young Bigfoot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Baby_Bigfoot, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Baby_Bigfoot.cfg:18
msgid "This is custom unit. Its coding was done by Ravana and art by Mechanical."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Baby_Mudcrawler, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Baby_Mudcrawler.cfg:4
msgid "Baby Mudcrawler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Baby_Mudcrawler, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Baby_Mudcrawler.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Mudcrawlers are magical constructs of soil and water. They attack by belching"
" lumps of mud at their foes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Bigfoot, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Bigfoot.cfg:4
msgid "Bigfoot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Bigfoot, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Bigfoot.cfg:18
msgid "This is custom unit. Its coding and art were done by Ravana."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Cuttle_Fish, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Cuttlefish.cfg:4
msgid "Cuttle Fish"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Cuttle_Fish, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Young_Cuttle_Fish, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#. [unit_type], id=AE_stf_triththa_Giant_Squid, race=AE_stf_triththa_cuttlefish
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Cuttlefish.cfg:19
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Young_Cuttlefish.cfg:18
#: .\units\EOS_units\cuttlefish\Giant_Squid.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Cuttle Fish are gigantic creatures of the seas. They can grab their opponents"
" with strong tentacles, or spit a poisonous black ink from a distance. The "
"best way to survive an encounter with these monsters is to remain ashore."
msgstr ""

#. [chance_to_hit], id=AE_ext_ink
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Cuttlefish.cfg:52
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Young_Cuttlefish.cfg:48
msgid "Ink reduces opponents chance to hit by 15%"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Dragon, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Fire Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Dragon, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Dragon.cfg:27
msgid ""
"A dragon is a legendary creature, normally seen only in fantastic tales. They"
" are very rare, and were it not for the historical events, the singlehanded "
"destruction of cities and towns that these creatures have wrought, they might"
" be dismissed as mere myth. Legends are very specific about the ravages of "
"dragons; noting their great strength, speed, their preternatural cunning, and"
" above all else, the great fire that burns inside of them.\n"
"\n"
"Battling a dragon is said to be the pinnacle of danger itself, fit only for "
"fools, or the bravest of knights."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Guardian, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Guardian.cfg:4
msgid "Fire Guardian"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Guardian, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Warrior_Spirit, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Guardian.cfg:19
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Warrior_Spirit.cfg:22
msgid ""
"Fire Guardians are spirits of smoke and flame. No one is exactly sure where "
"they come from, but they are occasionally summoned by powerful mages to do "
"their bidding. When not being controlled they like to frolic in pools of lava"
" and take great delight in burning anything they can reach."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Fire_Warrior_Spirit, race=AE_ext_monsters_elemental
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Fire_Warrior_Spirit.cfg:4
msgid "Fire Warrior Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Giant_Rat, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Giant_Rat.cfg:4
msgid "Giant Rat"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Giant_Rat, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Giant_Rat.cfg:23
msgid ""
"Given an adequate supply of food, some rats can grow to truly impressive "
"sizes. They can also grow quite aggressive."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Giant_Yeti, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Giant_Yeti.cfg:4
msgid "Giant Yeti"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Giant_Yeti, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Giant_Yeti.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Little is known about Yetis, ape-like creatures said to live in remote and "
"snow-covered mountains. Few profess to have seen one, and their existence is "
"doubted by many."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Gryphon.cfg:4
msgid "Gryphon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Elder_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Gryphon.cfg:18
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Gryphon_Elder.cfg:18
msgid ""
"These majestic and powerful creatures are masters of the sky. Gryphons are "
"both dangerous and wary of other intelligent creatures, and thus should not "
"be disturbed without a good reason."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Elder_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Gryphon_Elder.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Gryphon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Mudcrawler, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Mudcrawler.cfg:4
msgid "Mudcrawler"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Mudcrawler, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Mudcrawler.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Giant Mudcrawlers are a larger kind of Mudcrawler, and are magical constructs"
" of soil and water. They attack by belching lumps of mud at their foes, or by"
" striking them with their fists."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Overgrown_Scorpion, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Overgrown_Scorpion.cfg:4
msgid "Overgrown Scorpion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Overgrown_Scorpion, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Scorpion, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Overgrown_Scorpion.cfg:33
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Scorpion.cfg:18
msgid ""
"A normal scorpion is dangerous enough — the deadliness of one the size of a "
"man needs little explanation."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Overgrown_Spider, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Overgrown_Spider.cfg:4
msgid "Overgrown Spider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Overgrown_Spider, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Overgrown_Spider.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Giant Spiders are said to roam the depths of Knalga, devouring many victims. "
"They have a vicious bite and can also fling webs through the air to trap "
"their prey."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Red_Dragon, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Red_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Red Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Scorpion, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Scorpion.cfg:4
msgid "Scorpion"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Sea_Serpent, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Sea_Serpent.cfg:4
msgid "Sea Serpent"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Sea_Serpent, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Sea_Serpent.cfg:22
msgid "Sea Serpents are gigantic monsters, capable of capsizing boats by themselves."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Skeletal_Dragon, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Skeletal_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Skeletal Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Skeletal_Dragon, race=undead
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Skeletal_Dragon.cfg:32
msgid ""
"Long ago one of the mightiest living creatures, the feared Dragon has become "
"only bones and dark sinew. Long after its death, it was raised through the "
"dark powers of necromancy, which it now serves. The Skeletal Dragon may look "
"like nothing more than a pile of bones, but few people who thought that way "
"lived long enough to change their minds."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Water_Serpent, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Water_Serpent.cfg:5
msgid "Water Serpent"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Water_Serpent, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Water_Snake, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Water_Serpent.cfg:32
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Water_Snake.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Scholars differ as to the ancestry of the Water Serpent. Some hold that they "
"are the immature young, or mature cousins, of Sea Serpents. Others hold them "
"up as a primitive offshoot of the Nagas. What is certain is that it is wise "
"to avoid waters where they are known to congregate."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Water_Snake, race=AE_ext_monsters_seacreatures
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Water_Snake.cfg:5
msgid "Water Snake"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wingless_Dragon, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wingless_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Wingless Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Wolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Direwolf, race=wolf
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Great_Wolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf.cfg:32
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Dire.cfg:18
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Great.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Wolves are aggressive animals that hunt in packs. Although weak individually,"
" a wolf pack can kill even the strongest man in minutes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Direwolf, race=wolf
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Wolf_Dire.cfg:4
