msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Young_Gryphon, race=gryphon
#: .\units\EE_units\monsters\Young_Gryphon.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Gryphons, when young, are covered with white and gray feathers. As soon as "
"they can fly, they become able to defend their nests and to attack intruders."
" Though not yet powerful as adult Gryphons, underestimate them is a dangerous"
" thing to do, a foolish move that led many poachers to death, either by "
"facing their claws or falling down from a mountain while trying to escape a "
"Gryphon's rage."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Naga Fighter
#: .\units\EE_units\nagas\c1-Fighter.cfg:9
msgid ""
"The serpentine naga are one of the few races capable of any meaningful "
"mobility in water, giving them mastery of a whole world effectively forbidden"
" to land dwellers. Still, they are not true creatures of the sea, and their "
"inability to breathe water leaves them in trepidation of the abyss. They are "
"small, and somewhat frail in form, but often much more nimble than their "
"opponents."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Leader
#: .\units\EE_units\orcs\b1-Leader.cfg:15
msgid ""
"Unusually cunning orcs tend to find themselves as the leaders of warrior "
"bands. They carry a crossbow out of necessity, but are much more skilled with"
" the sword. These orcs are powerful fighters, but they also have a certain "
"rapport with their kin, especially goblins, and can inspire them to fight "
"with uncharacteristic boldness."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Ruler
#: .\units\EE_units\orcs\b2-Ruler.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Any orc who can keep a large tribe from feuding and in-fighting is often "
"unusually intelligent and commanding, and is inevitably very strong as well. "
"They are skilled with both sword and crossbow, but their real talent lies in "
"their rare ability to rally other orcs to battle, to give orders that are "
"followed not out of fear, but loyalty."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Orcish Sovereign
#: .\units\EE_units\orcs\b3-Sovereign.cfg:14
msgid ""
"From time to time, an orc will arise who has a natural charisma and command "
"over his ilk. If he is also strong and cunning enough to survive early "
"leadership struggles, he will inevitably find himself leading a great horde "
"of warriors, and he will also inevitably cause a great deal of trouble for "
"the civilized races of the world. The surest way to disperse such a host is "
"to slay this rare orc who can hold it together."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Archwitch, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Archwitch.cfg:4
msgid "Archwitch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Archwitch, race=human, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Cunning_Woman, race=human, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Witch, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Archwitch.cfg:33
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Cunning_Woman.cfg:30
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Witch.cfg:32
msgid ""
"This unit is from the Golden Age. Its coding and art where done by "
"ForestDragon.\n"
"\n"
""
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Archwitch, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Archwitch.cfg:35
msgid ""
"Archwitches have a wide knowledge of the nature which she can use against her"
" enemies. She can now cast poisoned thorns which are hard to direct mostly in"
" retaliations. Archwitches are respected by any magician considering that all"
" her training and knowledge was acquired autodidactly and no-one taught her. "
"Usually witches and Archwitches are few, and rarely they interact with others"
" in their lives before being recruited by the same outlaw army in where they "
"usually meet each other."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Archwitch.cfg:68
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Cunning_Woman.cfg:62
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Witch.cfg:63
msgid "dispell"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Cunning_Woman, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Cunning_Woman.cfg:4
msgid "Cunning Woman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Cunning_Woman, race=human, gender=female
#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Witch, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Cunning_Woman.cfg:32
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Witch.cfg:34
msgid ""
"Sometimes even in marginality places there are people with talents in magic. "
"Usually men living in corrupt ambients have no time to even notice if they "
"had potential to magics, so some of those outlaw men could have talents for "
"magic, but sadly they will never have time to wonder if they had or not "
"talent for magics. Unlike in the case of men, women doesn't have that "
"physical strength so many of them while childhood experimented a lot of "
"different things... also for the surprise of some of these women they have "
"talent for magic arts. Usually outlaws steal a lot of things, some of those "
"magical books that almost nobody uses at all, also few cunning women "
"autodidacts themselves in order to learn how to heal their wounded outlaw "
"companions. Once they gain enough experience their foes' names them Outlaw "
"Witches and when they start being feared by the enemies who face them they "
"are named as Archwithches."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_Great_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\d3-Great_Ogre.cfg:4
msgid "Great Ogre"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_Great_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\d3-Great_Ogre.cfg:24
msgid ""
"Great Ogres are giant creatures that usually live alone in the wilderness, "
"remarkably similar to humans in form, though large and misshapen. While they "
"can be easily outrun or outsmarted, their strength is not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_outlaws_Witch, race=human, gender=female
#: .\units\EE_units\outlaws\Witch.cfg:4
msgid "Outlaw Witch"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=Troll Whelp
#: .\units\EE_units\trolls\a1-Whelp.cfg:9
msgid ""
"Describing a troll as a whelp is something of an oxymoron, given that their "
"bodies are already much hardier than that of a grown man. They are clumsy and"
" not yet capable of walking properly, forced instead to shamble about on all "
"fours, but any difficulty this causes them is more than made up for by the "
"raw strength of their race."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_northerns_Troll_Shaman, race=troll
#: .\units\EE_units\trolls\a2-Shaman.cfg:4
msgid "Troll Shaman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_northerns_Troll_Shaman, race=troll
#: .\units\EE_units\trolls\a2-Shaman.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Troll shamans are the mystical leaders of the trolls. Though not as strong or"
" tough as other trolls, their true power lies in their fire magic, which they"
" use to blast enemies with gouts of fire or punish enemies with curses."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Flame_Dragon, race=AE_ext_monsters_monster
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Flame_Dragon.cfg:4
msgid "Flame Dragon"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Ogre.cfg:4
msgid "Ogre"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Ogre.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Ogres are giant creatures that usually live alone in the wilderness, "
"remarkably similar to humans in form, though large and misshapen. While they "
"can be easily outrun or outsmarted, their strength is not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Young_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Young_Ogre.cfg:4
msgid "Young Ogre"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_ext_monsters_Young_Ogre, race=ogre
#: .\units\EE_units\unused\Young_Ogre.cfg:20
msgid ""
"When still young, Ogres are sometimes captured and taken into armies to be "
"trained. They cannot manage weapons skillfully, but they compensate for that "
"lack with great strength."
msgstr ""

