msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Fighter, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Fighter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Guardsman, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Guardsman.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Guardsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Guardsman, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Guardsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"The dwarven race has always been famed for its sturdiness of build, and many "
"of their warriors outfit themselves to take advantage of this. Dwarven "
"guardsmen march into battle with tower shields and spears. Most often, their "
"role is to hold the line, and to take a heavy toll on those who try to break "
"it. As the line marches forward, they act to secure its hard-won advance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lord, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lord.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Lord"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Lord, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Lord.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Clad in shining armor, these dwarves look like kings from under the "
"mountains. They wield axe and hammer with masterful skill, and can hit a "
"target with a thrown hand axe at several paces. Though slow on their feet, "
"these dwarves are a testament to the prowess of their kin."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Sentinel.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Sentinel.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Champions among their fellow troops, the dwarven sentinels form the bulwark "
"of their battle lines. Leading a direct assault against a line that they "
"fortify, is often out of the question; it tends toward being suicidal, rather"
" than merely ineffectual. Equipped with the strongest of Knalgan armor, these"
" dwarves are masters of the melee and can hold a patch of earth with the "
"single-minded tenacity of an oak."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Ghost, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Spirit"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Ghost, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Though they can travel through most terrain without hinderance, their "
"dwarvish form is still relatively slow."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Wraith, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit_Ancestor.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Ancestor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Wraith, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit_Ancestor.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Dwarves have a deep connection to their history and culture. To preserve the "
"ancient way, they often ask for advice from those that came before them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Spectre, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit_Forefather.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Forefather"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Spectre, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Spirit_Forefather.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Necromancer? I hardly know her.\n"
"\t\n"
"Forefathers were the most renowned warriors, craftsmen and researchers of "
"their time. It would be a waste if all that knowledge and talent dies with "
"them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Stalwart, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Stalwart.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Stalwart"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Stalwart, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Stalwart.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The wiles of experience and training turn guardsmen into worthy soldiers. "
"These stalwart troops are equipped to match their skills, and can hold their "
"ground against all but the most visceral assault. It is a dangerous thing to "
"lose a foothold to one such as these, for it will not be easily reprised."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Steelclad, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Steelclad.cfg:4
msgid "Dwarvish Steelclad"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_dw_Steelclad, race=AE_RHY_dwarf
#: .\units\RE_units\dwarves\Steelclad.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Outfitted in the strongest plate and mail of Knalgan forges, the Steelclads "
"are the vanguard of dwarvish armies. They are renowned for their resilience "
"in the heat of battle, and their mastery of both battleaxe and warhammer make"
" them imposing foes indeed."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose.cfg:4
msgid "Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Rarely seen even by elves, the Wose is an order of creature about which "
"little is known. The elves are the source of most of this knowledge; they "
"know that these beings are not descended from trees, despite the similarity "
"in form, and they know that a wose is more closely tied to the faerie world "
"than the elves themselves, though in a different way. The motives and "
"workings of their kind are unknown, though most subscribe to the obvious "
"theory that woses are dedicated wardens of the natural world.\n"
"\n"
"Woses are utterly unwarlike, but possess a great strength. They are, however,"
" neither used to, nor quick at moving around."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Ancient_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose_Ancient.cfg:4
msgid "Ancient Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Ancient_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose_Ancient.cfg:17
msgid ""
"There is a curious story of a farmer who had a great oak in his lawn, a tree "
"which had stood when his father first broke the soil on that land, and under "
"which his family had many memories. It was thus a shock to him, one morning, "
"when he awoke to find nothing but a bare patch of earth where the tree once "
"stood, as though it had been spirited away in the wee hours of the night.\n"
"\n"
"Such encounters are all that is known of what are presumably the most ancient"
" of woses."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Elder_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose_Elder.cfg:4
msgid "Elder Wose"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ey_Elder_Wose, race=wose
#: .\units\RE_units\elyser\Wose_Elder.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Woses have been said to possess many shapes, all of them tree-like in form, "
"and as they age, to increase in size. Tales tell of woses who resemble trees "
"in this respect as well, towering over the creatures who walk beneath them. "
"This is the greater part of why they are so rarely seen — standing in the "
"slumber which they so often do, a wose of that stature appears to be nothing "
"more than an oddly-shaped tree. Even a careless elf can sometimes be fooled.\n"
"\n"
"Woses are not warriors by any means, but their great strength can easily be "
"turned to violence, should someone manage to raise the ire of these "
"creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel.cfg:4
msgid "Angel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel.cfg:16
msgid "With their speed and the ability to fly, Angels are often used as scouts."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Archer, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_archer.cfg:4
msgid "Angel Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Archer, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_archer.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Angel archers harass enemy soldiers with their bow while staying out of their"
" range with their flying ability."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_archer.cfg:45
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_Marksman.cfg:48
msgid "enchanted arrow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_Marksman.cfg:4
msgid "Angel Marksman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Marksman, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_Marksman.cfg:17
msgid "While flying the angel marksmen have superior perception and accuracy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Seraph, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_Seraph.cfg:4
msgid "Seraph"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Seraph, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_Seraph.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Seraph have been influenced by arcane magic for many decades. This resulted "
"in higher affinity to magic and some mutations in their body. Most Seraphs "
"emit a holy aura, which boosts the morale of lawful allies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Angel Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Angel_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Angel_warrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The Angel warriors amplify their damage by using the extra speed when diving "
"down on the enemy."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Archangel, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Archangel.cfg:4
msgid "Archangel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Archangel, race=AE_RHY_angel
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Archangel.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Archangels carry magical flaming swords and are capable of using magic to a "
"small degree."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Crossbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Luz crossbowmen are miliz soldiers from lower classes. Though they posses "
"only cheap equipment, they can be deadly in range and melee."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Heavy_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman_heavy.cfg:4
msgid "Luz heavy Crossbow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Heavy_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman_heavy.cfg:20
msgid ""
"While not rich by any means, these veteran crossbowmen can at leat afford "
"decent equipment."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Arbalist, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman_war.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Arbalist"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Arbalist, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman_war.cfg:21
msgid "The best crossbowmen equip themself with a powerful arbalest."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Crossbowman_war.cfg:35
msgid "arbalest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inquisition_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitons_warrior.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Inquisition Warrior"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inquisition_Warrior, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitons_warrior.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Equipped with blessed weapons, the Inquisition warriors are a bane for evil "
"creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitons_warrior.cfg:36
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor.cfg:37
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_knight.cfg:38
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_paladin.cfg:39
msgid "holy sword"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=blade, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitons_warrior.cfg:45
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor.cfg:55
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor_fighter.cfg:33
msgid "chakram"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inquisitor, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Inquisitor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inquisitor, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor.cfg:17
msgid "Inquisitors defend their faith with all means."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor.cfg:46
msgid "firesword"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inq_Initiate, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor_fighter.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Inquisiton Initiate"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Inq_Initiate, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\inqisitor_fighter.cfg:16
msgid ""
"The Initiates of the Inquisition are recruited from noblemen and veteran "
"soldiers. For the promise of salvation, the Initiates spread their religious "
"belief through the land, if necessary  with their sword."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Tormentor, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_tormentor.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Tormentor"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Tormentor, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_tormentor.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Whomever stand in the way of the Inquisition is used as scapegoat to control "
"anger in the common folk. The Tormentors bring justice and pain to witches "
"and non-believers."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Holy_Warden, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_warden.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Warden"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Holy_Warden, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_warden.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The Order of Holy Wardens is build out of the most devoted and most brutal "
"followers of the faith. Equiped with a flail that ends in three heavy chains "
"and a big shield they hunt heathens and heretics"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Witchhunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_witchhunter.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Witchhunter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Witchhunter, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\mace_witchhunter.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Under the impression, they do the holy deed, the witchhunters carry out the "
"dirty work of the Inquisition."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Abbot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Abbot.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Abbot"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Abbot, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Abbot.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Abbots are the leaders in their monastery. Their status is well respected in "
"society. While not as enlightened as the clerics, their wisdom and healing "
"ability makes them the more reliable force in times of war."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Bishop, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Bishop.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Bishop"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Bishop, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Bishop.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Bishops are high ranking priests and councellors of the pope. They interpret "
"the holy word and create laws accordingly."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=arcane, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Bishop.cfg:53
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Cleric.cfg:51
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:53
msgid "lightwave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Cleric, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Cleric.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Cleric"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Cleric, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Cleric.cfg:17
msgid "Clerics are good preachers and insire the lawful around them."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Monk, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Monk.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Monk"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Monk, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Monk.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Monks chose a secluded life in a monastery to study. Their bodies are "
"strenghtened form hard labour and they've amassed a general knowledge of "
"herbalism."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Priest, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Priest.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Priest"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Priest, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Mage_Priest.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Many Priests come from the lower classes, but, in return for preaching the "
"holy word, they get access to knowledge and can eventually reach the rank of "
"cleric."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Miliz, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Militia"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Miliz, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz.cfg:17
msgid "Instead of trained soldiers, the Luz use men from lower classes en masse."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Peasant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_peasant.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Peasant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Peasant, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_peasant.cfg:22
msgid ""
"The peasants in the Luz theocracy are born into a miserable life. Due to "
"missed harvests and poor education many suffer from physical and mantal "
"problems. Usually the peasants are exempt from military service, but in times"
" of need they have to take up arms as well."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Keeper, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_pike.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Keeper"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Keeper, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_pike.cfg:16
msgid ""
"With experience and better equipment, the Keepers can form a strong defensive"
" wall."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_sentinel.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Sentinel"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Sentinel, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_sentinel.cfg:17
msgid "Sentinels act as guardians for high ranking Priests."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Veteran, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_veteran.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Veteran"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Veteran, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\miliz_veteran.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Veterans are jack of all trades. Instead of working as guards, they'll take "
"odd jobs from mercenary guilds or lords. The veterans are usually faster on "
"foot, capable swordsmen, and have recieved enough blessings to obtain a small"
" magic resistance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Pope, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:6
msgid "Luz Pope"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Pope, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Before he became pope, Cary earned the title of saint due to his gentle "
"nature. He himself would never hurt a living being, but his personal guard "
"will make any effort to protect him."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:36
msgid "guards"
msgstr ""

#. [swarm]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:46
msgid "swarm 4"
msgstr ""

#. [swarm]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\Pope.cfg:47
msgid "The more wounded this unit is the less attacks they get, to the minimum of 4"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_knight.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Knight"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Knight, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_knight.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Additionally to the normal sword, Luz Knights have a blessed weapon as symbol"
" of their status."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Paladin, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_paladin.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Paladin"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Paladin, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_paladin.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Paladins are as quick with their blade as they are with their horse. The holy"
" sword is devestating to the undead and magical creatures."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_rider.cfg:4
msgid "Luz Rider"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_lz_Rider, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-luz\rider_rider.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Luz Riders belong to the Inquisition. They are fast while still being "
"decently armored."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Castellan, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Castellan.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Castellan"
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Castellan.cfg:34
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Castle.cfg:29
msgid "hot oil"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Castle_Crossbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Castle.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Siege Defender"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Long.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Longbowman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Longbowman, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Bow_Long.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Longbows are fearsome weapons, but too difficult for beginning archers to "
"wield. It takes great strength to draw one, and the added range and power it "
"confers remain useless unless one has good aim with the weapon. Longbowmen "
"carry their weapons as a badge of pride, and most bowmen look forward to the "
"day they can begin using one."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Inflitrator, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E1_infiltrator.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Inflitrator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Inflitrator, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E1_infiltrator.cfg:17
msgid ""
"In ther inconspicuous civilian clothes, an Inflitrator can get behind the "
"enemy by hiding amongst the common folk."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E1_infiltrator.cfg:47
msgid "female^Regis Inflitrator"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Spy, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E2_Spy.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Spy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Spy, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E2_Spy.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Disguising as villager, bribing guards, intimitating people or using "
"counterfeit documents. Spies have many ways to infiltrate the enemy. How they"
" get there is not important. What really counts is waht they can do in their "
"position.\n"
"\t\n"
"To avoid getting caught, spies don't carry weaponry - at least not in a way "
"that can be seen. But once the enemy turn their back towards them, they use "
"the opportunity to strike."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E2_Spy.cfg:75
msgid "female^Regis Spy"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Jester, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E3_Jester.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Jester"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Jester, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E3_Jester.cfg:18
msgid ""
"These funny entertainers are not suspicious at all. Why would an assassin try"
" to stand out?"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\E3_Jester.cfg:80
msgid "female^Regis Jester"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Horseman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horseman.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Horseman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Hussar, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horse_Hussar.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Hussar"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Hussar, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horse_Hussar.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Hussars are the hidden ace of the regis army, either sweeping in at dawn to "
"drive back the forces of the night or giving them a last chase at dusk while "
"the main army can retreat."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Jouster, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Horse_Jouster.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Jouster"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_White_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage_White.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Healer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_White_Mage, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage_White.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Some magi, as they learn about the world around them, and learn the truth of "
"the suffering and squalor in which humanity too often lives, find that they "
"cannot bring themselves to be cloistered into a life of study. These men and "
"women give up the life of a mage, and join monastic orders, dedicating the "
"skills they have been given to the good of all. After their ordination, they "
"often travel the world, ministering to sickness and injury.Though not trained"
" for combat, they are a potent ally against magical or unnatural things."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Mage_White.cfg:101
msgid "female^Regis Healer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Halberdier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Palace Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Halberdier, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Spear_Halberdier.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Exceptional Pike users may learn how the use of a halbert and act as guards "
"in high prestige places. Some might even protect the royal palace itself."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Pikeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Spear_Pike.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Pikeman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Pikeman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Spear_Pike.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Promising spearmen in the armies of Wesnoth are often graduated to wielding "
"pikes, and are outfitted with something far superior to the motley collection"
" of leather armor they wore as recruits. A pike is a much longer weapon than "
"a spear, and thus facilitates different combat tactics. A wall of pikemen is "
"the bane of any cavalry charge, and with proper discipline and tactics, "
"pikemen can also hold most other infantry at bay."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Squire, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\sword-squire.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Squire"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Swordsman.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Swordsman"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Swordsman, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Swordsman.cfg:17
msgid ""
"An experienced soldier will often save enough to equip himself with a suit of"
" scale or chain armor, and a sturdy broadsword. Though trading their spears "
"for swords can be a jarring change, most spearmen will leap at the chance, "
"knowing all too well the limitations of the weapon they are leaving behind. A"
" sword is not without its own drawbacks, but is more versatile than a spear, "
"and much better in close quarters."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Royal_Guard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Sword_Guard.cfg:4
msgid "Regis Royal Guard"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_rg_Royal_Guard, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\human-regis\Sword_Guard.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Royal Guards are picked from the best swordsmen. Serving under any of the "
"higher nobility, they function as bodyguards, and partly as a badge of office"
" for their employers. A special force of Royal Guards is stationed at the "
"capital, guarding the palace grounds and the royal family. Because of their "
"trusted relationship to their superiors, they, rather than mercenaries, are "
"often deployed on missions of crucial import. Their reliability and mastery "
"of close combat are their best assets, for which they are well-renowned."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Archer, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer.cfg:4
msgid "Skeleton Archer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Archer, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer.cfg:17
msgid ""
"A skeleton archer is little different from the ‘skeletons’ which often "
"accompany it — it is a sin against nature, a warrior raised from the dead to "
"fight once again. In their masters’ hands, these soldiers will do anything to"
" achieve the tasks laid before them, for death holds no fear for one who is "
"already dead."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Banebow, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bane.cfg:5
msgid "Banebow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Banebow, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bane.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The most powerful of the undead archers invariably end up being those who "
"were themselves archers in their previous life. They wander the fields of "
"battle, guided by the fading memory of their former skill, neither knowing, "
"nor caring what their purpose or foes might be. They are driven only by a "
"malice born of their empty and tortured existence."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bane.cfg:55
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bone.cfg:45
msgid "acidic arrow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Bone_Shooter, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bone.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Shooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Bone_Shooter, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_bone.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Of a dark sorcerer’s creations, some take more strongly to the false life "
"given them. The potency of their unlife is given equipment to match; archers,"
" in particular, are often outfitted with a truly vile arsenal. Their quivers "
"are filled with shafts made not of wood, but of the bones of their victims. "
"It follows that they are dubbed simply ‘Bone-Shooters’ by their unfortunate "
"enemies."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Fire_Shooter, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_fire.cfg:4
msgid "Fire Shooter"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Fire_Shooter, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\archer_fire.cfg:19
msgid ""
"With enough magic it is possible to stack effect above another. Burning "
"Skeletons are often unintentionally created when a rookie Necromancer tries "
"to get creative and typically don't last very long.\n"
"Trained Mages however cast fire resistance spells on the bodies and will add "
"them as valuable soldiers to their army."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_construct, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_construct.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Construct"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_construct, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_construct.cfg:17
msgid ""
"If you have power to bestow life upon corpses, why would you stop at what "
"nature gives you? Once Necromancers have figured out, that you can combine "
"dead bodyparts at your leasure, there was no stopping to their creativity.\n"
"\t\n"
"Bone constructs have been assembled from the remains of many different "
"creatures. They can have many different looks -depending on what was "
"available to the animating Mage at the time- , but usually have features that"
" aid them in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=pierce, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_construct.cfg:29
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_giant.cfg:45
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_golem.cfg:26
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_mess.cfg:32
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_snake.cfg:50
msgid "pointed bone"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_giant, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_giant.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Giant"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_giant, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_giant.cfg:17
msgid ""
"I'm sure some of these bones are from dragons and I'm really concerned with "
"how they got those."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_giant.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Compared to the lower levels, this unit is so huge that it does not defend "
"well on most terrain."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=impact, range=melee
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_giant.cfg:54
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_golem.cfg:35
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_mess.cfg:41
msgid "bash"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_golem, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_golem.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Golem"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_golem, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_golem.cfg:17
msgid ""
"As soon as these creatures stop resembling humanoids, it doesn't matter what "
"bones you use. They can even repair themself by sticking the remains of "
"whatever they kill in ther own body. And they kill a lot."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_mess, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_mess.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Mess"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_mess, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_mess.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Something clearly went wrong here. But let's reanimate it anyway to see what "
"it does."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_snake, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_snake.cfg:4
msgid "Bone Snake"
msgstr ""

#. [advancement], id=amla_bone_snake
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_snake.cfg:20
msgid "longer bones"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_bone_snake, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\bone_snake.cfg:38
msgid "With parts mostly from ripcages and spines, these undead move like snakes."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghast, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghast.cfg:4
msgid "Ghast"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghast, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghast.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The ghast is a creature taken from humankind’s most primal nightmares. Unlike"
" their lesser cousins, ghouls and necrophages, ghasts are not patient enough "
"to wait for their victim to die from poison before consuming the body. They "
"attack directly with their enormous mouths, trying to rip the flesh straight "
"from their foes. Once their enemy is defeated, they eat the rest of the body,"
" gaining strength in the process."
msgstr ""

#. [special_note]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghast.cfg:26
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghoul.cfg:31
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Necrophage.cfg:25
msgid ""
"Compared to mainline, this unit has better 'impact' resistance and more HP, "
"but worse 'arcane' resistance."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghoul, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghoul.cfg:4
msgid "Ghoul"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghoul, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Ghoul.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Only the more perverse and sadistic of necromancers know what must be done to"
" turn a person into a ghoul, and it is a secret they are not telling. The "
"result, however, is all too well known; it is a beast that knows nothing of "
"its days as a human being, a creature that shambles about as naked as the day"
" it was born, and gorges itself on the flesh of the dead.\n"
"\n"
"It is because of such things that necromancy is condemned with an almost "
"primal hatred in all civilized lands."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Necrophage, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Necrophage.cfg:4
msgid "Necrophage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Necrophage, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Corpse_Necrophage.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The necrophage, or ‘devourer of the dead’, is a monstrous, corpulent thing, "
"which bears only a crude resemblance to a man. They appear to be quite rotten"
" in spite of their ability to move; they are rife with disease and poisons of"
" the blood, and have a stench to match. But the most revolting fact about "
"these creatures, apparent only to those who can perceive the traces of foul "
"magic on them, is that they were somehow made from living men — a process "
"about which almost nothing is known, but which can be nothing but "
"nightmarish."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Burning_Lich, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_lich.cfg:4
msgid "Burning Lich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Burning_Lich, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_lich.cfg:18
msgid ""
"The burning Liches are a masterpiece of necromancy and pyromancy. Animated "
"skeletons are enhanced by fire spells to increase their resistance and turn "
"them into a burning nightmare. They do not posses magic on their own, instead"
" they concentrate the fire of their body to create fireballs."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Pyromancer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_necromancer.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Pyromancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Pyromancer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_necromancer.cfg:18
msgid "Plague creates Burning Liches instead"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Pyromancer, race=AE_RHY_human, gender=male
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_necromancer.cfg:33
msgid ""
"Mal Conar is not only a powerful Necromancer, but has mastered fire aswell. "
"He uses his abilities in combination to create his own race of undead."
msgstr ""

#. [attack], type=fire, range=ranged
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_necromancer.cfg:58
msgid "fire wave"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Black_Skeleton, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_skeleton.cfg:4
msgid "Black Skeleton"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Black_Skeleton, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\fire_skeleton.cfg:16
msgid ""
"When he raised the burned corpses of his parents, Mal Conar simultaniously "
"created a new kind of undead. The charred remains turned out very brittle, "
"but over years of research, Mal Conar perfected the arts. By putting in more "
"magic to strengthen the bones, the burned corpses do not have the weakness of"
" regular Skeletons anymore. Their body is also hot enough to burn their "
"enemies on touch."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Necromancer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necromancer.cfg:4
msgid "Necromancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Necromancer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necromancer.cfg:21
msgid ""
"One of the pinnacles of what is considered ‘black magic’ is the art of "
"necromancy, the terrible ability to awaken the dead with false life. This "
"discovery alone caused humanity’s condemnation of black magic, for the "
"nightmarish things it has made real have given fear a vast new arsenal.\n"
"\n"
"This ability, in all aspects, is the first step towards cheating death of its"
" ultimate prize."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necromancer.cfg:154
msgid "female^Necromancer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Dark_Adept, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Adept.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Adept"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Dark_Adept, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Adept.cfg:23
msgid ""
"To attract any practitioners, the lure of black magic must be a great prize "
"indeed, for anyone caught practicing the art in the civilized world is "
"subject to a death sentence. And yet there are those who pursue this art, for"
" the prize offered is nothing less than immortality. Hidden away in secret "
"cults, or initiated into the dark orders of the underworld, the training "
"which these fanatics must endure often drives them to exhaustion and "
"enfeeblement.\n"
"\n"
"In such condition, their only weapon is the craft they have so committed "
"themselves to learning.\n"
"\n"
"Though the first Necromancers were humans, this kind of magic also spread to "
"other races. For elves this ended in a civil war and the creation of "
"darkelves. Even now some practitioners come from the once noble race."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Adept.cfg:163
msgid "female^Dark Adept"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Dark_Sorcerer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:4
msgid "Dark Sorcerer"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Dark_Sorcerer, race=AE_RHY_human
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The dread inspired by black magic is enhanced by the secrecy and fell rumors "
"which surround it. Dark sorcerers have begun to unlock the secrets of life "
"and death, the latter of which is all too easy to inflict. This labor gives "
"the first glimmerings of the connection between the soul and inert matter, "
"and the first successful experiments in manipulating this bond. The terrible "
"unknown that lurks beyond death is glimpsed, and will inevitably be fathomed.\n"
"\n"
"Despite any design they may have of using this to wrest their own immortality"
" from nature’s grasp, the first results of their work have immediate, and "
"unpleasant applications. The life they breathe into dead matter can create "
"servants for them, servants which will work, but which will also kill, and "
"will never question their masters. These creations have a loyalty any tyrant "
"would dream of, and it is tempting to those with even the slightest desire "
"for power."
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:149
msgid "Dark Sorceress"
msgstr ""

#. [female]
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Dark_Sorcerer.cfg:153
msgid ""
"The dread inspired by black magic comes chiefly from how little is known "
"about it by the common man. Dark sorceresses have begun to unlock the secrets"
" of life and death, the latter of which is all too easy to inflict. This "
"labor gives the first glimmerings of the connection between the soul and "
"inert matter, and the first successful experiments in manipulating this bond."
" The terrible unknown that lurks beyond death is glimpsed, and will "
"inevitably be fathomed.\n"
"\n"
"Despite any design they may have of using this to wrest their own immortality"
" from nature’s grasp, the first results of their work have immediate, and "
"unpleasant applications. The life they breathe into dead matter can create "
"servants for them, servants which will work, but which will also kill, and "
"will never question their mistress. These creations have a loyalty any tyrant"
" would dream of, and it is tempting to those with even the merest desire for "
"power."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Lich, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Lich.cfg:4
msgid "Lich"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Lich, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_Lich.cfg:19
msgid ""
"A lich is the physical embodiment of black magic’s first goal: the quest to "
"achieve immortality. Though a great deal is sacrificed in the rebirth, in "
"becoming a lich one cheats death of that which truly gives it terror. For it "
"is the mind that is retained, and the spirit which follows, though the body "
"may wither away.\n"
"\n"
"It is not known, save perhaps by the inner circles of necromancy, whether "
"life is prolonged indefinitely or simply extended. The fact that this "
"question can be raised at all is a testament to the magnitude of what their "
"order has achieved."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Mage, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_skeleton.cfg:4
msgid "Skeleton Mage"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Skeleton_Mage, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Necro_skeleton.cfg:21
msgid ""
"Corpses raised from Wizards can sometimes retain enough of their memories and"
" intelligence to casts spells in their new undead form.\n"
"\t\n"
"Note: Despite levitating, these Mages have the same defense as normal "
"skeletons."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghost, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Ghost.cfg:4
msgid "Ghost"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Ghost, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Ghost.cfg:18
msgid ""
"Enslaved within a shroud of enchantments, a trapped spirit may be likened to "
"the wind in the sails of a ship. This damned vessel becomes an unfailing "
"servant which can be bound to whatever task their master sees fit."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Nightgaunt, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Nightgaunt.cfg:4
msgid "Nightgaunt"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Nightgaunt, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Nightgaunt.cfg:19
msgid ""
"The purpose of the masks that these creatures wear is unknown, as is the "
"countenance that they obscure. These terrible forms are rarely seen by the "
"living, and those who live to speak of them had no leisure to study their "
"foe."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Shadow, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Shadow.cfg:4
msgid "Shadow"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Shadow, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Shadow.cfg:18
msgid ""
"When light came into the world and gave form to the unknown, fear was forced "
"to retreat into darkness. Since that day, the shadows of the world have held "
"terror for humanity, though it knows not why.\n"
"\n"
"That is a question which is easily answered by a necromancer."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Spectre, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Spectre.cfg:4
msgid "Spectre"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Spectre, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Spectre.cfg:20
msgid ""
"Sometimes called the ‘hollow men’, spectres form the right arm of their "
"masters’ powers. They are an unholy terror to the living, for they are quite "
"as deadly as their appearance suggests.\n"
"\n"
"The creation of these is itself no mean feat, but the real danger in "
"encountering one is that it is likely only the harbinger of a much more "
"dangerous force that will follow in its wake."
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Wraith, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Wraith.cfg:4
msgid "Wraith"
msgstr ""

#. [unit_type], id=AE_rhy_ne_Wraith, race=AE_RHY_undead
#: .\units\RE_units\undead\Spirit_Wraith.cfg:18
msgid ""
"These shades of what were once warriors are among the most terrifying things "
"a necromancer can create, for a sword will cleave right through them as if "
"through air, seemingly without doing harm. It is the thought that these foes "
"are invincible which is so frightening, a notion that is fortunately far from"
" the truth."
msgstr ""
